<Docs title="Python SDK" description="Route, invoke, validate, and escalate model calls with tiny.router.">
  <p class="eyebrow">Python SDK</p>
  <h1>A provider-agnostic control plane.</h1>
  <p class="lead">The SDK chooses models but never owns credentials. Bring any model client; keep authentication, budgets, and observability in your application.</p>

  <h2>Route only</h2>
  <div class="code-window"><div class="code-bar"><i></i><i></i><i></i>route.py</div><pre><code><span class="token-key">from</span> tiny_router <span class="token-key">import</span> Router

router = Router.from_files(<span class="token-string">"model.json"</span>, <span class="token-string">"router.json"</span>)
result = router.route(
  <span class="token-string">"Prove this queue is linearizable"</span>,
  minimum_tier=<span class="token-string">"medium"</span>,
)

<span class="token-key">print</span>(result.tier.label)
<span class="token-key">print</span>(result.model)
<span class="token-key">print</span>(result.decision.confidence)</code></pre></div>

  <h2>Invoke, validate, escalate</h2>
  <p>If an output fails your task check, <code>execute</code> advances one tier at a time. Retryable provider errors also escalate; non-retryable errors stay visible.</p>
  <div class="code-window"><div class="code-bar"><i></i><i></i><i></i>execute.py</div><pre><code><span class="token-key">from</span> tiny_router <span class="token-key">import</span> ModelTarget, ProviderError

<span class="token-key">def</span> invoke(target: ModelTarget, prompt: str) -> str:
  <span class="token-key">try</span>:
    <span class="token-key">return</span> client.generate(model=target.model, prompt=prompt)
  <span class="token-key">except</span> TimeoutError <span class="token-key">as</span> exc:
    <span class="token-key">raise</span> ProviderError(str(exc), retryable=<span class="token-key">True</span>)

result = router.execute(
  prompt,
  invoke,
  validate=answer_passes_tests,
)

<span class="token-key">print</span>(result.output)
<span class="token-key">print</span>(result.escalated)</code></pre></div>

  <h2>Async providers</h2>
  <p><code>execute_async</code> mirrors the synchronous contract and accepts either synchronous or asynchronous validators.</p>
  <div class="code-window"><div class="code-bar"><i></i><i></i><i></i>async.py</div><pre><code>result = <span class="token-key">await</span> router.execute_async(
  prompt,
  invoke=async_provider_call,
  validate=async_task_check,
)</code></pre></div>

  <h2>Stable outputs</h2>
  <ul><li><code>RoutingResult</code> resolves tier, model, provider, confidence, probabilities, expected costs, and decision reason.</li><li><code>ExecutionResult</code> adds provider output and every attempted tier.</li><li>Configuration and returned model metadata are immutable.</li><li>Domain errors derive from <code>RouterError</code>.</li></ul>
</Docs>
